Local Development
 ├─ Activate venv
 │    source venv/bin/activate
 ├─ Test ML model
 │    python
 │    >>> import pickle
 │    >>> with open("backend/rf_model.pkl", "rb") as f: model = pickle.load(f)
 ├─ Test FastAPI endpoints
 │    uvicorn backend.main:app --reload
 │    Open http://127.0.0.1:8000/docs
 └─ Ensure async endpoints work (/ping, /traceroute, /dns, /speedtest)

Git / Version Control
 ├─ git add .
 ├─ git commit -m "Update backend / fix structure / add FastAPI main.py"
 └─ git push origin main

Render Deployment
 ├─ Procfile at project root
 │    web: uvicorn backend.main:app --host 0.0.0.0 --port $PORT
 ├─ requirements.txt includes scikit-learn + all dependencies
 ├─ Render builds virtualenv, installs packages
 └─ API runs; check logs for ML load & endpoints

Domain Setup (Optional)
 ├─ Point 3xample.ca DNS to Render service
 ├─ Ensure HTTPS works
 └─ Swagger UI accessible via https://3xample.ca/docs

✅ Tips
 ├─ Always test locally before pushing
 ├─ Keep rf_model.pkl inside backend/
 └─ Async endpoints: ping, traceroute, dns, speedtest


